item.title: The influence of age and gender on the covid-19 cases in Toronto
item.description: author:Duoyi Zhang date:2020-09-22 Abstract: This article is about digging the relationship between gender,age and covid-19 infection rate and recovery rate in Toronto. Despite the missing data and limitation of resources,the passage draws a conclusion that there exist a solid connection between age and the recovery rate.But there seem to be no difference beween the male and female in front of the covid-19.It can help people have a better understanding about the disease.

item.title: Some other knowledge you need to know about the reference
item.description: #What is City of Toronto Open Data? The City of Toronto’s Open Data Portal is an open source delivery tool to bring people and data together. Whether you’re an app developer, an engaged citizen, or a student trying to learn more about how the city works, the Open Data Portal contains a wealth of datasets for you to explore. We update regularly with new datasets, and welcome your requests. #About COVID-19 Cases in Toronto
